{
  "stem": "22869.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she entrusted this to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was-- you know, I felt good about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she felt like a relief.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't carry that burden now by myself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There is somebody else that shares it with me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It gives you--it gives you a little picture, even to me today, how much belief does a person have?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I speak to them on the street, or in the train, or in a plane-- and I tell them, look, I was in Auschwitz, and this and this happened.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He probably looks at me bewildered.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Come on, don't-- I mean, the world has read now, and saw in pictures enough to know better.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it's-- it's not plausible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's not plausible to believe that something like this can happen to you.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To me, it was-- it was even bigger news, was I never knew of the fact-- because we-- I was in the men's camp, not in the women's camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because we had to stay around for appell if a man disappeared.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the women had to stand around if the women-- but I never-- to me, the case wasn't known that a woman escaped Auschwitz, and she arrived.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you have to realize, also, that-- that we were subjected to all the punishments because somebody ran away.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We endured the punishment with happiness-- we were-- we were happy that somebody escapes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a chance in a million that the world outside will find out, and-- and maybe something will be done about it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, I recall now that sometime in 1943, in Birkenau-- I don't remember what period of time that was-- I received a package from the Swedish Red Cross-- two cans of sardines.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The sardines meant the world to me in 1943.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
